    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-06-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 407.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bingham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokio,
                                Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 9, 1885</date>. (Received July
                            13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2064.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 2056, dated the 30th
                        ultimo, wherewith I had the honor to inclose a copy of my note to his
                        excellency Count Inouye, dated the 29th ultimo, conveying, in pursuance of
                        your instruction, an expression of the thanks of our Government to that of
                        Japan for the timely service rendered by His Majesty’s troops at Seoul in
                        February last, I now have the pleasure to inclose herewith a translated copy
                        of Count Inouye’s reply thereto, dated the 8th instant.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JNO. A. BINGHAM.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
